        "new_string": "Flink's Kafka connector (org.apache.flink.connector.kafka.source.reader.deserializer.KafkaRecordDeserializationSchema) serves as the adapter that bridges these two interfaces. It wraps Kafka's Deserializer<T> and adapts it to work with Flink's DeserializationSchema abstraction. When Flink reads from Kafka, it uses KafkaRecordDeserializationSchema to take Kafka's ConsumerRecord and convert it using Kafka's built-in Deserializer implementations, while presenting the results as a Flink DeserializationSchema.\\n\\nA concrete example is SimpleStringSchema (org.apache.flink.api.common.serialization.SimpleStringSchema in flink-core/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/api/common/serialization/SimpleStringSchema.java), which implements both DeserializationSchema<String> and SerializationSchema<String>. This class demonstrates how Flink adapts byte-based serialization to its schema model, converting between byte arrays and String objects while maintaining type information for Flink's internal type system.\\n\\nKey differences:",
